# Backend Configuration

## Environment Variables
Create `.env` file:

```env
# Server
PORT=5001
NODE_ENV=development

# Database (Neon PostgreSQL)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host/database
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=mentor_db
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=password

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key
JWT_EXPIRY=7d

# CORS
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Features
ENABLE_RECORDING=false
MAX_SESSION_DURATION=3600000

# Email — Gmail SMTP (for session reminder emails)
# 1. Enable 2-Factor Auth on your Google account
# 2. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 3. Create an App Password for "Mail"
# 4. Paste it as EMAIL_PASS below
EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USER=your-gmail@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASS=your-gmail-app-password
EMAIL_FROM=MentorConnect <your-gmail@gmail.com>
```

## Development
```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

Backend runs on `http://localhost:5001`

## Features
- User authentication with JWT
- Real-time WebSocket connections with Socket.io
- PostgreSQL database with Neon
- REST API endpoints
- Code execution sandbox (via Piston)
- WebRTC signaling
- Session management
